---
Barbados (national)
Dominican Republic (national)

******
Mexico and Central America
---
Mexico
- Baja California Sur state. 25 Sep 2013. Dengue 214 cases; DHF/serious 10 cases. Municipalities most affected: San Jose del Cabo 97 cases, Cabo San Lucas 84 cases.
http://octavodia.mx/articulo/45696/aumentan-a-214-los-casos-de-dengue-en-bcs [in Spanish]

[Maps of Mexico can be seen at http://www.map-of-mexico.org/mexico-states.gif and http://healthmap.org/r/1wvK. - Mod.TY]

- Guerrero state. 25 Sep 2013. Dengue 1646 cases.
http://www.tabascohoy.com/2/notas/index.php?ID=150699 [in Spanish]

- San Luis Potosi state. 29 Sep 2013. Dengue 500 cases.
http://pulsoslp.com.mx/2013/09/29/en-alerta-contra-brote-de-colera/ [in Spanish]

- Tabasco state. 24 Sep 2013. Dengue as of 16 Sep 2013, 4577 cases; DHF/serious 998 cases; deaths (susp.) 10. Declining.
http://www.tabascohoy.com/2/notas/index.php?ID=150261 [in Spanish]

Costa Rica (national). 28 Sep 2013. Dengue as of 21 Sep 2013, 38 497 cases; DHF/serious 111 cases; no confirmed deaths. Most affected areas are Limon, Guanacaste and Puntarenas, both in the Pacific coast.
http://thecostaricanews.com/costa-rica-reports-38497-cases-of-dengue/16886

[The small number of DHF/serious cases without confirmed deaths suggests that Costa Rica has excellent surveillance that picks up milder cases.

Maps of Costa Rica can be accessed at http://geology.com/world/costa-rica-map.gif and http://healthmap.org/r/1kdD. - Mod.TY]

Honduras (national). 29 Sep 2013. Dengue 26 747 cases; DHF/serious 3485 cases; deaths 24. 293 of 298 municipalities affected. Municipalities most affected this past week Trujillo and Campamento with a total of 1196 cases. Declining.
http://www.latribuna.hn/2013/09/28/casos-de-dengue-llegan-a-26747-a-nivel-nacional/ [in Spanish]

[Maps of Honduras can be accessed at http://www.lib.utexas.edu/maps/americas/honduras.jpg and http://healthmap.org/r/1G7K. - Mod.TY]

Caribbean
---
Barbados (national). 25 Sep 2013. Dengue 511 cases; deaths (conf.) 1, (susp.) 1.
http://www.stabroeknews.com/2013/news/regional/09/25/dengue-high-in-barbados/

[Maps of Barbados can be accessed at http://www.picstropical.com/barbados/index-barbados/Barbados_Map.gif and http://healthmap.org/r/3DHu. - Mod.TY]

Dominican Republic (national). 25 Sep 2013. Dengue 9724 cases; deaths are increasing [number not given].
http://www.almomento.net/articulo/146109/RD-Mas-muertes-por-dengue-en-la-region [in Spanish]

[Maps of the Dominican Republic can be accessed at http://www.atozmapsdata.com/zoomify.asp?name=Country/Modern/Z_Domini_Pol2 and http://healthmap.org/r/1Hgf. - Mod.TY]
